==[[French]]==

==Etymology==
From [[French]] ''[[fleur]]'', "[[flower]]" + [[French]] ''[[de]]'', "from" or "of" + [[French]] ''[[sel]]'', "[[salt]]"; literally, "salt flower" or "salt blossom."

===[[Noun]]===
Floating salt crystals skimmed from the surface of evaporating ponds. 

====Quotations====
* '''2002''': ''"Egyptian salt from Alexandria was highly appreciated, especially their '''fleur de sel''', the light crystals skimmed off the surface of the water."'' - Mark Kurlansky, <cite>Salt: A World History</cite>